  "title": "Accountant/Finance Manager",
  "description": "<p>Job Description: </p><p>· Transaction Processing & Reconciliation: Managing accounts payable and receivable, ensuring invoices match purchase orders, and reconciling bank statements and balance sheet accounts.</p><p>· Financial Reporting & Closing: Leading the month-end and year-end close process, preparing journal entries (accruals, deferrals), and generating financial statements like balance sheets and income statements.</p><p>· Compliance & Audit Support: Maintaining strict adherence to GAAP, internal controls, and specific healthcare regulations. Preparing documentation and responding to auditor inquiries is critical.</p><p>· Inventory Accounting & Cost Management: A major focus. Accountants reconcile stock levels, track inventory held at third-party locations (vendor-managed inventory), manage cost of goods sold (COGS), and analyze manufacturing or procurement variances.</p><p>· Regulatory & Tax Compliance: Navigating a complex web beyond standard accounting rules. This includes healthcare-specific laws (e.g., Anti-Kickback Statute), FDA regulatory adherence impacting financial reporting, and managing multi-jurisdictional sales/use tax for distributors.</p><p>· Systems & Process Coordination: Using specialized software (like SAP or QuickBooks) and acting as a bridge between finance, sales operations, and the supply chain to ensure accurate financial data flow.<br /></p><p>Skills and Qualifications</p><p>· Education: A bachelor's degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field.</p><p>· Experience: At least 1-3 years in accounting, with experience in manufacturing, distribution, or healthcare being a significant advantage.</p><p>· Technical Skills: Advanced proficiency in Excel and hands-on experience with ERP systems (like SAP) or accounting software (like QuickBooks).</p><p>· Key Attributes: Meticulous attention to detail, strong analytical and problem-solving skills, and excellent communication abilities to collaborate across departments.</p>",
